#!F-adobe-helvetica-medium-r-normal--18*
#!N 
#!CSeaGreen #!N  #!Rgautax AutoAxes... #!N #!EC #!N #!N This option 
generates an axes box around an image: #!N #!N Select  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
AutoAxes... #!EF from the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options #!EF pull-down menu. The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
AutoAxes Configuration... #!EF dialog box appears, as illustrated in  #!Laxes160,dxall324 f Figure 60  #!EL  . 
#!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Raxes160 #!N Graphics omitted from Online Documentation. Please 
see the manual. #!N #!N Figure 60. AutoAxes Configuration dialog box 
#!EF #!N #!EC #!N #!N The dialog box consists of eight 
parts: #!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Enabled #!EF #!I50 
#!N The first "part" consists of a single toggle button--  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
AutoAxes enabled #!EF . This button must be activated (depressed) to 
make an axes box appear the next time the visual program 
is executed. (The button is automatically activated whenever one or more 
of the AutoAxes options are changed.) Releasing (deactivating) the button prevents 
the appearances of an axes box. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Input 
groups #!EF #!I50 #!N The second part of the dialog box 
displays six (6) of the available configuration options shown below. Depressing 
(enabling) any of these option buttons automatically expands the window appropriately 
to reveal the relevant options. Releasing (disabling) any of these option 
buttons removes the relevant options. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Axes' Labels 
#!EF #!I50 #!N Allows you to individually specify a label for 
each of the three axes: #!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   X, Y, Z #!EF #!I50 #!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!N 
#!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Miscellaneous #!EF #!I50 #!N Contains the following specifications: 
#!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Frame #!EF #!I50 #!N 
allows you to turn on or off a frame for the 
axes (that is, lines which complete the cube, in addition to 
the back three faces which are drawn by default). #!N #!I0 
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Grid #!EF #!I50 #!N allows you to turn on 
or off grid lines along major ticks. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Font #!EF #!I50 #!N allows you to choose a font for 
the labels. The ellipses button allows you to choose from the 
set of predefined fonts. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Label Scale #!EF 
#!I50 #!N allows you to change the size of the labels 
from the default size. For example, specifying a labels scale of 
2 will make the labels twice as large. #!I0 #!N #!N 
#!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Annotation Colors #!EF #!I50 #!N allows you 
to specify a color for each part of the axes: the 
grid (if drawn), ticks, labels, and background. The colors can be 
any of the defined colors (see  #!Lcolor,dxall792 h Color  #!EL  in IBM Visualization Data 
Explorer User's Reference), and in addition, the background can be drawn 
as "clear" (invisible). #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Corners / Cursor #!EF 
#!I50 #!N The Corners section allows you to explicitly set the 
range of the axes in each dimension. The Cursor section allows 
you to place a cursor (marker) at a specific location in 
the axes box. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Ticks #!EF #!I50 #!N 
Allows you to specify number or locations of ticks. If the 
option menu to the right of "Ticks" is set to "All," 
then you can specify the approximate total number of ticks in 
the "All" field. If the option menu to the right of 
"Ticks" is set to "Per Axis," then you can specify the 
approximate number of ticks on each axis. If the option menu 
to the right of "Ticks" is set to "Values," then you 
can use the Ticks' Values section to set exact tick locations 
and labels. You can also specify the direction of the ticks 
to point inward or outward using the buttons at the bottom 
of this section #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Ticks values #!EF #!I50 
#!N This section is only enabled if the option menu to 
the right of Ticks is set to "Values" By using the 
... buttons you can add Tick Location/Tick Label pairs for each 
axis. See  #!Lautoaxe,dxall770 h AutoAxes  #!EL  in IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's Reference for 
more information. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   buttons #!EF #!I50 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
OK #!EF and  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Apply #!EF both confirm option changes, which 
appear the next time the visual program is executed.  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   OK 
#!EF also closes the dialog box. #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Restore #!EF 
and  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Cancel #!EF both restore values that were present when 
you opened the dialog box or last clicked on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Apply #!EF button.  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Cancel #!EF also closes the dialog box. 
#!I0 #!N #!N #!N #!N #!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Raxes261 #!N Graphics 
omitted from Online Documentation. Please see the manual. #!N #!N Figure 
61. Expanded AutoAxes Configuration Dialog Box. The box lists seven options 
not visible in the default version (  #!Laxes160,dxall324 f Figure 60  #!EL  ). #!EF #!N 
#!EC #!N #!N For more details on the AutoAxes configuration, see 
the corresponding module description in IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's Reference. 
Note: It is also possible to set AutoAxes parameters using input 
parameters to the Image tool (see Image in IBM Visualization Data 
Explorer User's Reference). #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF #!N 
